      "content": "but you're missing the logic though. if the sum is always zero regardless of the variables, then there's no logical reason to prefer the 'staying' path over the 'leaving' path. if they are mathematically equivalent, then choosing the exit isn't a failure, it's just picking one of two equal values. isn't that just a rational way to look at it?",
